        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Equivalency of input parameters Gradation 3 criteria",
        "description": "FEA model inputs (geometry, material properties, boundary conditions) directly matched to measured specimen characteristics. Discrepancies between nominal and as-built dimensions quantified and incorporated as input uncertainty. Equivalency mapping table documented in assessment report."
      },
      "rationale": "FEA geometry derived from CAD nominal dimensions adjusted by CMM measurements of actual test specimens (mean deviation 0.03 mm, max 0.08 mm). Material properties from same certified MTR lot as bench specimens. Boundary conditions replicate F1717 fixture geometry within 0.5 mm. Equivalency mapping table (Appendix B of assessment report) documents all input-to-specimen correspondences. No unresolved equivalency gaps identified. Gradation 3 achieved."
