        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Relevance of QoI Gradation 3 criteria",
        "description": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) directly map to the clinical performance parameters specified in the FDA guidance for spinal pedicle screw systems. QoI relevance matrix documented in assessment report."
      },
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and FDA guidance for pedicle screw 510(k) submissions. These QoIs directly characterize the failure modes relevant to the clinical COU (fatigue fracture, permanent deformation under physiological loading). QoI relevance matrix (Appendix A) maps each QoI to the corresponding clinical risk. Gradation 3 achieved."
